<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="45" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1485,2016]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1521,1547]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: A swan-sized anatid in which the distal humerus is little expanded ventrally, the tuberculum supracondylare ventrale is not distinctly ventral to the shaft, is flattened rather than elevated facing somewhat distally, elongate and extends well proximal to the condylus dorsalis, and is widely separated from but proximally surpasses the distal end of a small ovate fossa musculi brachialis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
