Group, 19–16 Ma, early Miocene (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Worthy, T. H. &amp; Scofield, R. P. &amp; Salisbury, S. W. &amp; Hand, S. J. &amp; De Pietri, V. L. &amp; Blokland, J. C. &amp; Archer, M." box="[308,522,1809,1835]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" pagination="87 - 107" refId="ref10921" refString="Worthy, T. H., Scofield, R. P., Salisbury, S. W., Hand, S. J., De Pietri, V. L., Blokland, J. C. &amp; Archer, M. (2022) A new species of Manuherikia (Aves: Anatidae) provides evidence of faunal turnover in the St Bathans Fauna, New Zealand. Geobios, 70, 87 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. geobios. 2021.08.002" type="journal article" year="2022">
Worthy 
